    "## 3. Training Data Collection Approach\n",
    "\n",
    "### Data Sources for AI Training\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Conversation Analysis\n",
    "- **User message patterns**: Vocabulary, sentence structure, communication style\n",
    "- **Response preferences**: What types of responses get positive feedback\n",
    "- **Topic interests**: Areas where user engages most deeply\n",
    "- **Emotional expressions**: How user expresses different emotions\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Feedback Collection\n",
    "- **Explicit ratings**: 1-5 star system for AI responses\n",
    "- **Implicit feedback**: Message length, response time, follow-up questions\n",
    "- **Correction data**: When user corrects or guides the AI\n",
    "- **Preference indicators**: User reactions to different AI personalities\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Behavioral Patterns\n",
    "- **Interaction timing**: When user prefers to chat\n",
    "- **Session length**: How long conversations typically last\n",
    "- **Question types**: What kinds of questions user asks\n",
    "- **Context switching**: How user moves between topics\n",
    "\n",
    "### Galileo Integration for Training Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Extend the existing Galileo logging system to capture training-specific data:\n",
    "\n",
    "```typescript\n",
    "interface TrainingLog {\n",
    "  userId: string;\n",
    "  aiPersonalityId: string;\n",
    "  interaction: {\n",
    "    userMessage: string;\n",
    "    aiResponse: string;\n",
    "    responseTime: number;\n",
    "    userFeedback?: number; // 1-5 rating\n",
    "    correctionProvided?: string;\n",
    "  };\n",
    "  trainingMetrics: {\n",
    "    communicationStyleScore: number;\n",
    "    personalityAlignmentScore: number;\n",
    "    knowledgeAccuracyScore: number;\n",
    "    creativityScore: number;\n",
    "  };\n",
    "  timestamp: Date;\n",
    "}\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Training Data Analysis Framework\n",
    "\ndef analyze_conversation_patterns(user_messages):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Analyze user communication patterns for AI training\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    patterns = {\n",
    "        'avg_message_length': sum(len(msg.split()) for msg in user_messages) / len(user_messages),\n",
    "        'common_words': {},  # Would implement word frequency analysis\n",
    "        'question_ratio': sum(1 for msg in user_messages if '?' in msg) / len(user_messages),\n",
    "        'exclamation_ratio': sum(1 for msg in user_messages if '!' in msg) / len(user_messages),\n",
    "        'formality_score': 0.5,  # Would implement formality detection\n",
    "        'emotional_tone': 'neutral'  # Would implement sentiment analysis\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    return patterns\n",
    "\ndef calculate_training_effectiveness(before_scores, after_scores):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Calculate how effective a training session was\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    improvements = {}\n",
    "    total_improvement = 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for category in before_scores:\n",
    "        improvement = after_scores[category] - before_scores[category]\n",
    "        improvements[category] = improvement\n",
    "        total_improvement += improvement\n",
    "    \n",
    "    effectiveness_score = min(100, max(0, total_improvement * 20))  # Scale to 0-100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'effectiveness_score': effectiveness_score,\n",
    "        'category_improvements': improvements,\n",
    "        'overall_improvement': total_improvement\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n# Example usage\n",
    "sample_messages = [\n",
    "    \"Hey, how are you doing today?\",\n",
    "    \"I was wondering about my astrological chart...\",\n",
    "    \"That's really interesting! Tell me more.\",\n",
    "    \"Can you help me understand my Mars in Capricorn?\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n,
    "patterns = analyze_conversation_patterns(sample_messages)\n",
    "print(\"Communication Patterns:\")\n",
    "for key, value in patterns.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {key}: {value}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example training effectiveness\n",
    "before = {'communication': 60, 'personality': 45, 'knowledge': 70}\n",
    "after = {'communication': 75, 'personality': 55, 'knowledge': 80}\n",
    "effectiveness = calculate_training_effectiveness(before, after)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nTraining Effectiveness: {effectiveness['effectiveness_score']}%\")"
   ]
